The worst bond film ever made.

The last one was so good and they should have stopped with this film being painful to watch.

This film is as far as I can see the last bond film ever and has killed my love of the franchise.

I was fucked over by this and not having a movie that celebrates masculinity that was expected and with my money being stolen I was subjected to going throw 3 hours of painful torture.

Fuck the studio system for letting something that so many love be destroyed by a list of people who new what they where doing was going to upset a lot of people.

It’s one year later and I’m still very angry and haven’t forgotten who was responsible for destroying my Bond movie experience.

They should never be let to work on any film projects again and all band from future studio projects.

This movie was anything but fitting.

It was the Bond movie fans didn’t want and has destroyed it for ever.

Even Daniel Craig said he wasn’t happy with it and has apologised to disappointed and angry fans for taking part in what he understood was going to be a different kind of Bond movie all together.

Letting fan’s down like this should be an offence and the people responsible should be made accountable for what they have done.

It’s not just a movie, it’s an experience that people payed for and where at the end of the day cheated out off there money and expectations with this being just unforgivable by a studio to create and profit from with not giving the fans what was promised to them.
